Package: Pinference
Title: Probability Inference for Propositional Logic
Version: 0.2.5
Authors@R: c(
  person("PierGianLuca", "Porta Mana", ,
  "pgl@portamana.org", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6070-0784"))
  )
Description: Provides a function to calculate the lower and upper bounds of the probability for a propositional-logic expression, given constraints on the probabilities for other expressions. The function also works for truth-valuation in the style of sequent calculus. It requires the 'lpSolve' package.
